---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Aside from '../../../components/Aside.astro';
import {mathsSidebar} from '../../../data/maths-sidebar';
import {Code} from 'astro:components';
---

<DocsLayout title="Easing Functions" sidebar={mathsSidebar}
            description="28 easing functions for animations and transitions">

    <h1>Easing Functions</h1>

    <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 !mt-2 !mb-8">
        28 easing functions in four categories: basic, In, Out, and InOut.
    </p>

    <h2>The Ease.Fn interface</h2>

    <p>Every easing function implements <code>Ease.Fn</code>, which takes a progress <code>Double</code>
        (0.0&ndash;1.0) and returns the eased value. You can create custom easing functions with
        <code>easeFn</code>:</p>

    <Code code={`import io.peekandpoke.ultra.maths.Ease

// Use a built-in function
val result = Ease.Out.cubic(0.5)  // 0.875

// Create a custom easing function
val custom = Ease.easeFn { x -> x * x * x }  // same as cubic In`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Basic easing</h2>

    <div class="not-prose my-8">
        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
            <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Function</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Behavior</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-gray-400">
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.linear</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Constant speed &mdash; output equals input</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.stuck</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Always returns 0.0 &mdash; no progress</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.immediate</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Always returns 1.0 &mdash; instant completion</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <h2>Ease.In &mdash; start slow, accelerate</h2>

    <div class="not-prose my-8">
        <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
            <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Function</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-white font-semibold">Curve</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-gray-400">
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.In.sine</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Sinusoidal acceleration</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.In.quad</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Power of 2 (x&sup2;)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.In.cubic</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Power of 3 (x&sup3;)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.In.quart</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Power of 4</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.In.quint</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Power of 5</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.In.pow(n)</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Custom power (x&#x207F;)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.In.circ</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Circular arc</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.In.elastic</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Oscillating spring overshoot</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td class="py-2"><code>Ease.In.bounce</code></td>
                <td class="py-2">Bouncing ball effect</td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <h2>Ease.Out &mdash; start fast, decelerate</h2>

    <p>Same set of curves, mirrored: <code>Ease.Out.sine</code>, <code>.quad</code>, <code>.cubic</code>,
        <code>.quart</code>, <code>.quint</code>, <code>.pow(n)</code>, <code>.circ</code>,
        <code>.elastic</code>, <code>.bounce</code>.</p>

    <Code code={`// Ease.Out starts fast and decelerates
val x = Ease.Out.bounce(0.7)  // bouncing deceleration at 70% progress`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Ease.InOut &mdash; accelerate then decelerate</h2>

    <p>Combines In and Out: accelerates through the first half, decelerates through the second.
        Available: <code>Ease.InOut.sine</code>, <code>.quad</code>, <code>.cubic</code>,
        <code>.quart</code>, <code>.quint</code>, <code>.pow(n)</code>,
        <code>.elastic</code>, <code>.bounce</code>.</p>

    <Aside>InOut does not include <code>circ</code>. If you need it, compose it with <code>easeFn</code>.</Aside>

    <Code code={`// Smooth start and end — good for UI transitions
val opacity = Ease.calc(
    from = 0.0,
    to = 1.0,
    progress = 0.5,
    fn = Ease.InOut.cubic,
)`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Binding to a range</h2>

    <p><code>bindFromTo</code> locks an easing function to a specific numeric range. The result is itself an
        <code>Ease.Fn</code>, so it composes with everything else:</p>

    <Code code={`val scroll = Ease.InOut.quad.bindFromTo(from = 0, to = 1000)

// At various progress points:
scroll(0.0)   // 0.0
scroll(0.25)  // 125.0
scroll(0.5)   // 500.0
scroll(0.75)  // 875.0
scroll(1.0)   // 1000.0`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <h2>Time-based easing</h2>

    <p><code>timed()</code> creates an easing that uses wall-clock time via the
        <a href="/ultra/datetime/kronos">Kronos</a> clock. Call it repeatedly to get the current eased value:</p>

    <Code code={`import kotlin.time.Duration.Companion.milliseconds

val anim = Ease.Out.elastic.timed(
    from = 0,
    to = 100,
    duration = 600.milliseconds,
)

// In a render loop or coroutine:
val value = anim { progress, done ->
    // progress: 0.0 to 1.0
    // done: true when duration has elapsed
}

// Or just check:
if (anim.isDone) { /* animation complete */ }`} lang="kotlin" theme="vitesse-dark"/>

    <Aside>Pass a test <code>Kronos</code> instance to <code>timed()</code> to control time in tests.
        No flaky timing-dependent assertions.
    </Aside>

    <div class="not-prose mt-8 flex gap-4">
        <a href="/ultra/maths/distributions"
           class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-brand-600 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-brand-500 transition-colors">
            Distributions &rarr;
        </a>
    </div>

</DocsLayout>
